title: For Sale:  low-cost
postcontent:
Excellent condition.  And a s the saying goes: “A revolver never lets you down!”  

I'm a private collector and, as part of a multi-gun lot in a recent auction, picked up an excellent .38 Special revolver.  It doesn’t fit in with the rest of my collection, so I’m offering it for sale, but not before testing it thoroughly at my local range. It is in great shape; is spot-on accurate; and will be an excellent, low-cost self-defense or carry gun for a new owner.  

The revolver is a Llama Ruby Extra, made in the 1960s in Spain by the Llama-Gabilondo y Cia company to compete globally with Smith & Wesson’s Model 10 as a police issue sidearm.  This Llama has features that actually make it nicer than the Smith & Wesson police gun, including a grooved backstrap for a better grip and a grooved top strap to cut down on haze in the sight radius.   I don't own a Model 10, but do have a S&W Model 64, the stainless version of the Model 10.  One of the photos shows the Llama and the Model 64 side by side for comparison.  

The Llama Ruby Extra sold well to police departments in South America and the Philippines but this one must have been shipped directly to the US as it is not import-marked.  The bore/lands/grooves are in great condition and the gun has just a trace of finish wear at the muzzle, so it seems to have spent more time in a sock drawer than a holster. 

Face-to-face sale not possible, but I’ll ship to a FFL-holder/firearms retailer near you for $20 or deliver to an FFL-holder in the NW Chicago suburbs for free.  Payment by money order or personal check is okay; just enclose a copy of the FFL license with your payment.  Item will be shipped only to the address on the license.  I have an FFL (03) license (the “curio and relic collector” license) and will send a copy of my license when shipping the gun.  Make sure your retailer is okay with accepting a shipment from an FFL (03) holder 

Just the Llama is for sale at this price.  The gun stand, Model 64 and bore light are for illustration only. 

Call REDACTED or contact by me via email at REDACTED.  (Please call only between 9 a.m. and 9 p. m. Central Time).

title: For Sale:  Ideal, low cost self-defense revolver:  Llama .38 Special
postcontent:
Excellent condition.  And, as the saying goes: “A revolver never lets you down!”

I'm a private collector and, as part of a multi-gun lot in a recent auction, picked up an excellent .38 Special revolver. It doesn’t fit in with the rest of my collection, so I’m offering it for sale, but not before testing it thoroughly at my local range. It is in great shape; is spot-on accurate; and will be an excellent, low-cost self-defense or carry gun for a new owner. 

The revolver is a Llama Ruby Extra, made in the 1960s in Spain by the Llama-Gabilondo y Cia company to compete globally with Smith & Wesson’s Model 10 as a police issue sidearm. This Llama has features that actually make it nicer than the Smith & Wesson police gun, including a grooved backstrap for a better grip and a grooved top strap to cut down on haze in the sight radius. 

The Llama Ruby Extra sold well to police departments in South America and the Philippines but this one must have been shipped directly to the US as it is not import-marked. The bore/lands/grooves are in great condition and the gun has just a trace of finish wear at the muzzle, so it seems to have spent more time in a sock drawer than a holster. 

Face-to-face sale not possible, but I’ll ship to a FFL-holder/firearms retailer near you for $20 or deliver to an FFL-holder in the NW Chicago suburbs for free. Payment by money order or personal check is okay; just enclose a copy of the FFL license with your payment. Item will be shipped only to the address on the license. I have an FFL (03) license (the “curio and relic collector” license) and will send a copy of my license when shipping the gun. Make sure your retailer is okay with accepting a shipment from an FFL (03) holder 

Call REDACTED (no texts) or contact by me via email at REDACTED.   (Please call only between 9 a.m. and 9 p. m. Central Time).

title: For Sale:  Collectors: Vintage Browning Hi-Power P35 Belgian Made, WW2 German Army, Tangent Sites, 9mm
postcontent:
Collectors: Vintage Browning Hi-Power P35 Belgian Made, WW2 German Army, Tangent Sites, 9mm

This is a WW2-era (early 1940’s) 9mm Browning Hi-Power.  It was made for Browning by Fabrique Nationale (FN) in Belgium for the German army.  The Nazi eagle appears on the slide, frame and barrel.

This is a blued gun, and in excellent shape for a vintage gun.  All parts are original and in perfect working order.  The slide, barrel and frame all have original matching serial numbers.  This is a rare WW2 Hi-Power with tangent sites, which allow for quick and easy distance adjustments.

Also included is a black leather flap holster.  I'm not sure if it is an original WW2 holster or not, but I can send you pictures so you can see if it is or not for yourself.

The various marking on the gun read:
FABRIQUE NATIONALE D’ARMES DE GUERRE
HERSTAL BELGIQUE
BROWNING’S PATENT DEPOSE
WaA140
(Serial Number) 130379

According to one writer (http://www.acant.org.au/Articles/GermanBrowningHiPower.html), the serial number on this gun places its production date on or before 1943.

The 14-round magazine appears to be an original, but is not the best: it looks like someone removed and welded back on the bottom of the magazine.  It still works fine and additional magazines are easy to come by.

This was my grandfather’s for many years, and came to me about ten years ago.  The story from him was that a friend of his in Redmond, OR took it off "a dead Nazi" during the war and brought it home.

I have put about 100 rounds of 115 grain 9mm ammunition through it without any problems.  I don’t have a need for it anymore and hope it will find a happy home with a collector who appreciates fine vintage guns like this.

FTF, cash transaction ONLY in Salem, Oregon.  You must be able to legally purchase this handgun.

I can email more pictures if you’d like.  Call or email to set up a time to pick it up.

Asking $900 obo.

Thanks,
Andrew
REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Get informed people of Illinois! Your constitutional rights are being violated!
location: All and any!, Illinois, United States
postcontent:
Illinois:  Gun and Magazine Ban and Registration Schemes Pass in Senate Public Health Committee Tonight 
If you own a semi-automatic firearm or detachable magazine, they may be banned, taxed, and registered and you could easily become a felon unless you act NOW

Anti-gun legislators led by Senate President John Cullerton and backed by Governor Patrick Quinn (D) substituted and passed sweeping draconian gun and magazine bans in the Senate Public Health Committee today.  House Bill 1263, amended to include a ban on many commonly owned firearms passed in this committee by a 6 to 4 vote.  House Bill 815, which was amended to include a magazine ban and shooting range restrictions, passed by a 6 to 3 vote.  Additionally, amendments have been filed to remove the hunting exception and could be introduced and considered on the Senate floor tomorrow.  These actions prove once again that Chicago politicians seem more focused on creating new classes of criminals out of law-abiding citizens than dealing effectively with their current violent crime problems.

New amendments have been introduced which add some specifics to the time limits for registration of previously owned firearms and magazines, and set the fees to register firearms and magazines. These amendments will be heard in the Executive Committee tomorrow morning at 11am. Both bills are expected to be heard on the floor of the Senate tomorrow afternoon for their third and final vote, and this is where the real fight will take place to maintain your Second Amendment rights and defeat Senate President Cullerton's anti-gun agenda.  It is imperative that you contact your state Senator IMMEDIATELY to express your opposition to House Bills 815 and 1263 and any additional anti-gun amendments.

Among other things, House Bill 815 would:

- Prohibit anyone without a FOID card from using a commercial shooting range, which in many cases would make it impossible to introduce new shooters to the safe and responsible use of firearms.

- Grant the State Police broad discretion to impose design, construction and operation standards that could shut down most commercial shooting ranges.

- Ban possession of magazines and other feeding devices that hold more than ten rounds of ammunition.  A "grandfather clause" would require registration by owners of such devices and give the State Police discretion to impose and charge fees.  Registration would require "proof of ownership" that could be impossible for most people to provide, and even registered owners could not transfer magazines within Illinois, except to an heir or a licensed dealer.  Transfers of "grandfathered magazines" would have to be reported to the ISP.

- Violations of this magazine ban would be a felony.  Failure to report theft or loss of a magazine would be a misdemeanor until the third violation, which would be a felony.

House Bill 1263 would:

- Ban, at a minimum, all detachable-magazine semi-automatic rifles and pistols. Remington 7400 deer rifles, Ruger 10/22 squirrel guns, Glocks, 1911s, etc. This ban would include about 80% of handguns now sold in the U.S.

- Possibly ban all semi-automatic rifles and even revolvers or single-shot pistols with the capacity to accept muzzle brakes or compensators.

- Ban "assault weapon attachments," so possession of a thumbhole stock, a pistol grip,or a fore-end (a "shroud" that "partially or completely encircles the barrel") would be a crime even if you didn't possess a firearm.

- Ban all .50 BMG rifles.

- Contains "grandfather" provisions that would require registration by owners of devices and give the State Police discretion to impose and charge fees. Registration would require "proof of ownership."

-  Create felony penalties for violation of this ban on guns or attachments.

- Create lost and Stolen penalties that would criminalize victims of gun theft.



Anti-gun politicians are attempting to sacrifice your constitutional rights as a scapegoat for the criminal acts of violence in Chicago by gangs and drug dealers.  Don't let them succeed in banning your firearms or magazines as an excuse for stopping criminals from misusing them.  Criminals -- by definition -- violate laws, especially gun control laws, including often: murder, rape, robbery, drug-dealing, gang violence, firearm theft, carrying concealed firearms without a license/permit, federal gun-free school zones. They do not obey gun bans, register their firearms, or get subjected to any gun control schemes (like the lone state ban on carrying concealed firearms for self-defense) that only affect and penalize law-abiding citizens like you. Your telephone calls TODAY will determine the outcome of this very serious assault on your Second Amendment rights.

The NRA-ILA will continue to send legislative updates as details become available.  However, it is of the utmost importance that you act NOW to stop this gun and magazine ban.  Call your state Senator IMMEDIATELY and express your opposition to banning firearms or magazines and urge them to vote against House Bills 815 and 1263.


To reach the main line for the Illinois General Assembly, please call REDACTED.

Contact information for your state legislators can be found by clicking here.

http://www.capwiz.com/nra/state/main/?state=IL&view=myofficials

postcontent:
Four-Day Defensive Handgun course at Front Sight Firearms Training Institute outside Las Vegas, NV.  Retail price: $2,000. 
This course is fast paced and exciting. The four day curriculum includes almost forty hours of training crammed into four intense days - there's very little down time! You spend many hours on the range performing live-fire exercises in addition to learning dry practice drills. You also attend several dynamic and thought-provoking classroom lectures. You will have an introduction to tactical training, and then you will have an opportunity to "clear" a live-fire shooting house simulator. Front Sight's unique teaching methods will bring you to the highest level of training offered by any training school in the industry. Even if you've never shot a gun before, or if you've been shooting for years, you're skills will improve dramatically. After completing the course you will have a complete understanding of the defensive handgun and a skill level that surpasses many of those who carry a gun for a living. Your gun handling, marksmanship, and tactical skills will be better than they've ever been and you will be able to safely and easily draw your weapon from a CONCEALED holster and fire two,sighted shots to the center of a target 5 yards away - all under 1.5 seconds!
For complete information on this course go to the following link: http://www.frontsight.com/courses/defensive-handgun-training-course.asp
I've taken several courses at Front Sight. Every time I've been on the range there's been law enforcement, military, and corrections personnel as well as private citizens on the range with me. My experiences at Front Sight have always been positive, so I purchased lifetime memberships for myself, my wife and my six children because I trust and believe in Front Sight! When we arrive at Front Sight we are treated with the utmost respect - in a friendly, supportive, and caring manner - by the absolute best trained, most consistent, and most effective instructional staff in the industry. Simply put - Front Sight provides the finest firearms training in North America!
You don't need to be an experienced shooter to take the course. I brought my 19 year old daughter who had never handled a BB gun, let alone a firearm. Upon completion of the course she understood basic tactical principles and had multiple opportunities to use her newly acquired skills under the stress of simulated, lethal encounters.
Friday-to-Monday...or Tuesday-to-Friday: You choose which portion of the week that's best for you to train.
Lecture Topics Include: Use of Deadly Force and the Law; Color Code of Mental Awareness; Stopping Power; Civil Liability, Concealed Carry; Course also includes Supplemental Lectures on Shotgun and Rifle topics
Firing Range Drills Include: Loading and Unloading; Grip, Stance, Sight Picture, Sight Alignment, and Trigger Control; Presentation from Ready and Holster; and Target Engagement from Arms Length to 15 yards under Time Pressure. Malfunction Clearing; Speed and Tactical Reloading; Tactical Training Simulation using Realistic Targets in Shoot/No Shoot Scenarios; Single Elimination Shoot-off, and Distinguished Graduate Skills Evaluation..Training starts at 8:00am each day and ends after 6:00pm each day.
Paperless Electronic Certificate: Your training certificate cannot get lost because it is provided in the form of an "Digital Certificate". I will send via email a Front Sight issued paperless, electronic certificate number directly to you upon receipt of payment. It will allow you to log into Front Sight's registration page at https://www.myfrontsight.com/secure/login.php and register for your course (or you can phone Front Sight to register). As long as you register for your course at least two weeks before the course date, you will be guaranteed a spot in the course you select. There is no expiration date on the course certificate once you purchase it. 
Prerequisite: None - no experience necessary.
Ammunition: You must purchase ammunition for your course. Approximately 600 rounds of ammunition are required for this course. You can purchase ammunition at Front Sight, or you can bring factory new ammunition (reloads are not allowed).
Handgun Rentals: You can rent a handgun, holster, belt, magazines, and magazine pouches from Front Sights Pro Shop. Front Sight provides a Glock 17 in 9mm as the standard rental gun (others may be available upon request). Contact the Front Sight Pro Shop at http://www.frontsightproshop.com/ You can also bring your own firearm and equipment. You must bring electronic hearing protection.
Background Check: A background check is required for all attendees with a $50 fee payable to Front Sight. Payment Method is via PayPal only. No exceptions. Basically, all the information you need is in this ad and in the two website links included above. So please take the time to review all the info before asking questions; however if you still have questions feel free to ask.
